postcontent:
I have a Beretta 84BB made in 1986, chambered in .380 ACP, in good condition, with some wear on the frame, and slight holster wear on the front end of the slide. The bluing is worn off on the safety, nad there is a little bit of wear on the grip panels. This model 84 is DA/SA and can be carried cocked and locked, and yes this means it does not have a decocker. It comes with two magazines (One well worn factory and one newer Mec-Gar), three sets of grips (Walnut Factory checkered, Rubber Pachmayr, and 1980s era smooth medallion wood), replacement slide and barrel (I replaced slide and barrel with immaculate condition ones that have been cerakoted matte black and kept the old ones, as the previous owner attempted to Duracoat them gloss black and did a poor job of it. They still function, but would shatter a mirror from lack of good aesthetics), a box of 25(+2 loose rounds) Hornady Critical Defense rounds, two IWB holsters (one custom leather and one factory Bianchi Leather), and a single Desantis Leather Magazine carrier, and factory blue Beretta Hard case (No manual) I am looking to part with. Also comes with spare guide rod and recoil spring and spare extractor. I carried this piece for a month or two, shot about 150 rounds down the pipe reliably with no failures, cleaned it, and stuck it in the safe after replacing the afore mentioned parts. Gun is reliable, accurate, fast, and fun to shoot. Magazines run flawlessly as well, even despite the beat up condition the factory mag is in. The gun has fed every ammo I fed it, including 50 or so of the Hornady Critical Defense. I just want to replace it with something I have more use for. Will do bill of sale. If you want more pics, just ask, I'll get them sent out. 
Thanks for looking.

The Seekins Precision Adjustable Gas Block lets you to fine tune your rifle's gas system for smoother cycling and operation. Regulating the amount of gas used to cycle the action allows tuning the rifle’s operation to a specific load and the use of low mass bolt carriers, buffers and springs to reduce felt recoil. This is critical to allow faster follow up shots, target acquisition and reliability.
The Seekins Precision Adjustable Gas Block is field adjustable. Operation is easy, simply turn the gas regulating screw in to lessen the amount of gas and out to add more gas, then use the brass set screw to lock the setting in place. The overall height of the gas block is 1.37” with left to right dimensions at .94” to fit under most hand guards and still have the customization of an adjustable gas block.

The MCSR V2 rail is designed so that the 3, 6, and 9 o'clock positions will now accept all keymod accessories and have two anti-rotation QD positions per side (6total). the internal dimension of the MCSR V2 has increased to 1.8" to accommodate most suppressors on the market.
